embargo. A version will move on the NYT wire at 9:30 p.m. EDT
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   CYBER-PRESIDENT _ WASHINGTON _ A look at the technological
skills of President Clinton, who will take part in an online chat
with the cyberpublic Monday evening. Does he use a computer? And if
so, why is it that he'll need someone to type his responses into
the computer when he responds to questions online? (Glass, Cox News
Service) MOVED
</P>
