<P>
   UNRESOLVED-RACEMURDERS (Birmingham, Ala.) _ All across the
South, unresolved, racially motivated murders from the civil rights
era, most of which have been ignored by authorities for decades,
are being reexamined, with a few being seriously investigated for
the first time. These long-ago slayings of blacks _ killings that
in some cases served as flashpoints in the civil rights movement _
are now going before grand juries and being prosecuted. A couple of
them have already resulted in convictions of aging white
defendants. With graphic. By Yellin.
</P>
<P>
   UPSCALE-FLEAMARKET (Monroe, Ohio) _ How prosperity has
transformed the weekend flea market from a place of cheap
hand-me-downs and nicked furniture to a market of deluxe items
where $900 to $9000 goods are not uncommon. In Monroe, whose famous
flea market attracts about 20,000 each day, the bartering and
exchanging goes on but now at designer prices. By Peter Kilborn.
</P>
