<P>
   SPECIAL-SECTIONS-MEDIA (Undated) _ Newspaper publishers have
long tried experiments to increase revenue, just as they have long
made financial investments in their communities. But the pressures
are now greater. The fiscal underpinnings of newspapers are
shifting, and their audience is slowly dwindling. But every
experiment entails a risk. Readers may suspect that the new
sections are written for advertisers, not for them. By Felicity
Barringer.
