(lb) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Treasury's schedule of financings this week includes
Monday's regular weekly auction of three- and six-month bills as
well as the government's quarterly refunding made up of a new
five-year note and the reopening of the April 10-year note due
2009.
</P>
<P>
   By the close of the New York cash market on Friday, traders
said, the rate on the outstanding three-month bill was 4.97 percent
and a six-month bill was 5.10 percent. In when-issued trading, the
five-year note was being offered at a price to yield 5.81 percent,
while the current 10-year issue was trading at a price to yield
5.91 percent.
