<P>
   FOOD-COLUMN-OWEN (Undated) _ On every level of Nagyesarnok _ the
105-year-old, brick-and-iron market building in Budapest _ you will
find paprika. You'll find ounces and pounds and probably a ton of
paprika. This is Hungary's red gold. The peppers grown on the Great
Hungarian Plain are slowly dried like prized coffee beans. They are
graded for quality like vintages of French wine.
</P>
<P>
   By John Owen. (Story has moved in the ``d'' category.)
