<HEADLINE>
LET'S GET READY TO BE HUMBLED (A NON-REGISTERED PHRASE)
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR; Last week, he was the warm-up act at Lambeau Field for the
Green Bay Packers' ``Monday Night Football'' game. The next night,
he helped the Clippers open the season at Staples Center. Later
this month, he'll be at the Hollywood Christmas Parade.
</P>
<P>
   The San Diego Chicken? Close.
</P>
<P>
   Think tuxedo.
</P>
<P>
   Michael Buffer, the ring announcer who doesn't even get 15
minutes but seems to have stretched his claim to fame long past its
expiration date, has been busy mucking up cyberspace when he isn't
cutting the ribbon to open a new K-mart garden department on his
busy schedule.
</P>
<P>
   But before venturing any further past the home page of the
official Michael Buffer Web site (www.letsrumble.com), be aware of
the fine print:
</P>
<P>
   &UR; +++ &LR; ``Let's Get Ready to Rumble!'' is a registered trademark of
Michael Buffer and Ready to Rumble, Inc., and does not fall under
BMI/ASCAP ruling. In addition, no commercial or promotional use of
this federally registered trademark phrase in audio or written form
is considered authorized unless permission is granted in writing by
Buffer Enterprises, Inc. &UR; +++ &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Next, we understand he's working on registering the phrases
``Please pass the salt'' and ``I'm sorry, but you'll have to repeat
that in English.''
</P>
<P>
   Of course, one can purchase a shirt or hat with the infamous
five-word phrase-turned-logo at the site's ``Buffer Zone''
merchandise area. Or find information about ordering the ``Ready 2
Rumble'' home video game. But the thing we'd really like to get our
gloves on is a disco hit (guess the title) that, according to his
site bio, once reached the top-20 sales charts in Germany.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; __  &LR; Internet voters will decide whom UCLA's women's basketball
team will face in the Nov. 20 Four in the Fall Tournament to be
televised on the Lifetime Channel.
</P>
<P>
   At Lifetime's site (www.lifetimetv.com/sports/
frameset.shtml/fourinfall99.html), the pairings of the tournament
that includes North Carolina, LSU and Texas Tech will be determined
by voting that runs through Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Imagine if ESPN tried that with a men's tournament.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; __  &LR; Coverage of the U.S. Lawn Mower Racing Association begins
Sunday on The Nashville Network, so for some background check _ or
as they say, to get the mowdown _ there's all the clippings you'd
ever want on the organization's Web site (www.letsmow.com).
</P>
<P>
   &UR; __  &LR; Kids today who've grown up with video-game versions of
baseball and football might even get a kick out of the electric
baseball and football games that remain solid sellers from Miggle
Toys/Tudor Games. Find out about the Electronic Football League,
how these games have progressed and where they can be bought on the
company's site (www.tudorgames.com/products. htm). &QL;
</P>
