<HEADLINE>
OFF THE WALL: GO FISH SOMEWHERE ELSE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   You shoulda seen the whoppers that got away from Fox while it
was trying to cram the ``When Wild Bass Get Caught on Tape''
tournament into its sports-programming lineup Sunday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
   Such as another episode of Pamela Anderson Lee in ``V.I.P.''
</P>
<P>
   Endless Wal-Mart commercials, debates about crankbait versus
spinnerbait and interviews with fish-catchers on Lake Lulu who were
thanking the Lord for helping them hook them big-mouths weren't
painful enough. In the end, no one seemed to know who had won the
darn-gum thing.
</P>
<P>
   ``If people haven't seen a weigh-in, they're in for a treat,''
said Joe Buck before the fiasco when the official-looking guy
throwing the fish into the bucket that apparently had a scale
underneath seemed to lose track of who was leading. In his ``Hey
Verne'' voice, he asked the guy in the sponsor-decorated shirt next
to him. He shrugged. Another guy walked in front of the camera.
</P>
<P>
   Finally, it was decided some cattle rancher from Oklahoma named
Darrel would be given the oversized check for $600,000.
</P>
<P>
   Yup, that !ital!was pretty special.
</P>
<P>
   So, hey, next time some out-of-touch high-level senior exec at
Fox gets some fish-fried idea to do something crazy during sweeps
month with good o' anglers who consider ``Smokey and the Bandit''
to be an American classic, kindly reel him in. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ With DRod on the rebound again _ a judge says he has to stay
500 feet away from Carmen Electra after their Miami Beach tussle _
cocktail waitresses and Keno runners across the country are on
grope alert. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Don't put another dime in Paul Hackett's jukebox. We don't
wanna see that play-calling no more. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Shawn Green need not worry that, at News Corp's annual
shareholders meeting last week, Sir Rupert of Murdoch said that
despite the company's need to grow rapidly he won't make any major
acquisition that will dilute earnings. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ With the movie rights to Muhammad Ali's life apparently
settled, Fox will go ahead later this month producing a two-hour
biopic on the life of ``The Greatest'' that will air sometime in
February. Thomas Carter _ Hayward from ``The White Shadow'' _ is
the executive producer. Ali is played by David Ramsey, who was also
in ``Three To Tango'' and ``Con Air.''
</P>
<P>
   Will Smith also wants to portray Ali in another bioflick
project. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ This Luc Robitaille broken foot by way of an errant puck
sounds way too much like what kept Rob Blake with his feet up most
of last season. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
