or inside their bodies. Using an array of tools and tactics, from a
huge SWAT team to electric stun shields to a program that
aggressively prosecutes inmates for crimes committed inside the
jails, correction officials have cut slashings and stabbings among
inmates by over 90 percent. Stabbing assaults by inmates have
plummeted from nearly 1,100 in 1994 to 78 so far this year.
