<P>
   (NYT26) NEW YORK -- Nov. 7, 1999 -- RUN-NY-MARA-WHEELCHAIRS-2,
11-7 -- Wheelchair competitors in the 1999 New York City Marathon
giving their all in a race in which for the first time none of them
were stopped along the course to let leading runners pass. Nine
wheelchair athletes, including two of the top three men's finishers
Sunday, filed suit against the New York Road Runners Club in July,
alleging that the marathon has discriminated against them not only
by delaying wheelchair racers to let top runners pass, but also by
denying them prize money and medals, which the elite runners
receive. (James Estrin/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
